@page "/docs-on-this-page"

<PageTitle>On This Page - Quark Suite</PageTitle>

<Div Space="Space.Y.Is8" MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Is4xl">
    <Section Space="Space.Y.Is4">
        <Paragraph TextColor="TextColor.MutedForeground">
            The docs rail scans this article for h2 and h3 headings with ids. The ignored preview below contains headings that should not appear in the right rail.
        </Paragraph>
    </Section>

    <Section Space="Space.Y.Is4">
        <H2 id="overview">Overview</H2>
        <Paragraph TextColor="TextColor.MutedForeground">
            OnThisPage builds a sticky table of contents from the rendered docs article DOM. The component defaults to the local data-docs-content article, so sidebars, headers, and unrelated page chrome are outside its scan.
        </Paragraph>
    </Section>

    <Section Space="Space.Y.Is4">
        <H2 id="scan-rules">Scan rules</H2>
        <Paragraph TextColor="TextColor.MutedForeground">
            Only h2 and h3 headings with ids are included by default. Empty headings and headings without ids are ignored.
        </Paragraph>
        <H3 id="heading-depth">Heading depth</H3>
        <Paragraph TextColor="TextColor.MutedForeground">
            Third-level headings render indented under second-level headings.
        </Paragraph>
        <H3 id="article-root">Article root</H3>
        <Paragraph TextColor="TextColor.MutedForeground">
            The default root selector is data-docs-content, which keeps the scan scoped to the docs article.
        </Paragraph>
    </Section>

    <Section Space="Space.Y.Is4">
        <H2 id="ignored-content">Ignored content</H2>
        <Paragraph TextColor="TextColor.MutedForeground">
            Use data-docs-ignore-toc on a container or heading to exclude nested headings from the rail.
        </Paragraph>
        <Div data-docs-ignore-toc Border="Border.Default" Rounded="Rounded.Lg" Padding="Padding.Is4" Space="Space.Y.Is3">
            <h2 id="ignored-preview-heading" class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Ignored preview heading</h2>
            <h3 id="ignored-preview-nested" class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight">Ignored nested heading</h3>
            <Paragraph TextColor="TextColor.MutedForeground">
                These headings are inside data-docs-ignore-toc and should not appear in the On This Page rail.
            </Paragraph>
        </Div>
    </Section>

    <Section Space="Space.Y.Is4">
        <H2 id="active-state">Active state</H2>
        <Paragraph TextColor="TextColor.MutedForeground">
            The active item updates while the article scrolls. The extra vertical space in this demo makes the active observer easier to verify.
        </Paragraph>
        <Div Height='Height.Token("h-[45vh]")' Border="Border.Default" Rounded="Rounded.Lg" BackgroundColor='BackgroundColor.Utility("bg-muted/25")'></Div>
        <H3 id="after-scroll">After scrolling</H3>
        <Paragraph TextColor="TextColor.MutedForeground">
            This nested section should become active when it reaches the top of the viewport.
        </Paragraph>
        <Div Height='Height.Token("h-[45vh]")' Border="Border.Default" Rounded="Rounded.Lg" BackgroundColor='BackgroundColor.Utility("bg-muted/25")'></Div>
    </Section>

    <Section Space="Space.Y.Is4">
        <H2 id="navigation-refresh">Navigation refresh</H2>
        <Paragraph TextColor="TextColor.MutedForeground">
            Navigate to another docs page and back to verify the rail refreshes after SPA route changes.
        </Paragraph>
        <Anchor To="accordions" Class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground underline underline-offset-4">
            Open Accordion docs
        </Anchor>
    </Section>
</Div>
